<Legal title="Terms of Service" updatedAt="May 2026" description="The terms that govern Hurricane Bath service.">
  <p>
    <em>This document is a draft. Final attorney-reviewed copy lands
    before the Hurricane Bath service opens to bookings in The Villages.</em>
  </p>

  <h2>The service</h2>
  <p>
    Dog Gone Clean operates a mobile dog bath service in The Villages,
    Florida, called the Hurricane Bath. Service includes a recirculating
    bath with adjustable pressure, a fresh water rinse, and drying in a
    climate controlled trailer. We bath only friendly dogs whose coats
    do not require a haircut.
  </p>

  <h2>Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    Pricing is set by coat tier (smoothcoat and doublecoat) at one
    inclusive price per visit. We do not charge add ons or surprise
    fees. Up to three dogs per visit; each additional dog is twenty
    dollars less than the prior dog in the same tier.
  </p>

  <h2>Card on file and billing</h2>
  <p>
    A card on file is required to book. Your card is charged at the
    24 hour mark before each scheduled visit, never sooner. Once
    inside the 24 hour window, the visit is locked and the payment is
    non refundable.
  </p>

  <h2>Skip and reschedule</h2>
  <p>
    You may skip one visit per rolling twelve months at no charge; the
    next visit after a free skip is charged at your normal rate. A
    second skip in the same window prices the next visit at the single
    visit rate (a real labor difference, not a fee). Rescheduling more
    than seven days from your original date steps the price up toward
    the single visit rate based on how far you move it.
  </p>

  <h2>Cancellation</h2>
  <p>
    You can stop your recurring subscription at any time, in two taps,
    from your client portal. No phone calls, no scripts, no questions
    asked. Any visit already charged inside the 24 hour window stays
    charged; future visits stop.
  </p>

  <h2>Eligibility</h2>
  <p>
    We bath dogs whose coats clean up fast and dry well, and who are
    handleable without aggression. A dog that shows aggression toward
    people is not eligible for this service. Coat types that mat or
    pack heavy undercoat against the skin are not eligible.
  </p>

  <h2>Limitation</h2>
  <p>
    We take reasonable care with every dog. If you provide a specific
    shampoo (medicated, prescription, or flea), we will use it, but we
    do not guarantee the result, which is between you and your
    veterinarian.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about these terms: contact details land before launch.
  </p>
</Legal>
